eslint & prettier with abnb style guide

packages to install
eslint-config-airbnb

install vs code extensions for eslint and prettier

websites
eslint (Gives examples of best practise for writing javascript)
arbnb style guide
prettier

include a custom config to personalize accordingly

vscode global settings
command ,
under text-editor check format on save
under prettier add check to use single quote

initialize a node project and save eslint dep locally
mkdir project_dir
cd project_dir
npm init -y
npm i -D eslint prettier eslint-plugin-prettier eslint-config-prettier eslint-plugin-node eslint-config-node

Add the airbnb style guide
npx install-peerdeps --dev eslint-config-airbnb

create config files for prettier and airbnb in the project root to hold custom rules
.prettierrc (see option rules on the prettier website)

install eslint globally then user a command to create a local config file

check for globally install packages in the npm
npm list -g --depth 0

install eslint globally
npm i -g eslint

now create a eslintrc.json config file in the project root
eslint --init

the file is reduced to extends/plugins and rules from the default configuration as
generated in the init command

edit the default .eslintrc.json config file add add custom rules as you see fit
see the file in this project as a starting point